# Summary
This documentation explains the behavior offset feature in Amplitude Analytics, which allows users to segment audiences based on behaviors across two distinct time periods, with examples including identifying repeat purchasers, targeting non-converting users, and detecting potential subscription churn by comparing user actions across different timeframes.

